com.linecorp.armeria.client

Interface Client

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CircuitBreakerClient, DecoratingClient, HttpTracingClient, LoggingClient, MetricCollectingClient

    public interface Client
    A set of components required for invoking a remote service.

    • Method Detail

      • newDecorator

        static <T extends ClientCodec,U extends ClientCodec,V extends RemoteInvoker,W extends RemoteInvoker> Function<Client,Client> newDecorator(Function<T,U> codecDecorator,
                                                                                                                                          Function<V,W> invokerDecorator)
        Creates a new function that decorates a Client with the specified codecDecorator and invokerDecorator.

        This factory method is useful when you want to write a reusable factory method that returns a decorator function and the returned decorator function is expected to be consumed by decorate(Function). For example, this may be a factory which combines multiple decorators, any of which could be decorating a codec and/or a handler.

        Consider using decorateCodec(Function) or decorateInvoker(Function) instead for simplicity unless you are writing a factory method of a decorator function.

        If you need a function that decorates only a codec or an invoker, use Function.identity() for the non-decorated property. e.g: 

        
 newDecorator(Function.identity(), (handler) -> { ... });
